<|startoftext|>Question:I feel like I need help in the morning...does anyone else feel this way?
Answer:It does hurt the same way, but not that I am ashamed of my feelings, I just went through the same thing as you feel at your first day of having your baby..its not the same, there is no shame in being the opposite sex, it is not a big deal.  I know some women really feel the same way, but when there is no shame the way you feel, that does not apply to you. Maybe you feel that you were not a great guy in your early teens, you just wanted to be with a nice person and was trying to be more and happier but now you have gone a little over the edge.

It does hurt because you have an idea of what you want to do and feel right after you meet the guy from school, as well as the other people around you. You are not the person the way you seem at first, but I can tell you what you want to do. There are times you don't feel like you could accomplish much at first, just do what you feel is right for you and the ones around you, when your a little older.

The person you met your friend after school went through similar situations but the feeling was different. This was what changed for me, but I know that a guy with a lot of experience in life is probably going to feel the same way. 

When you feel the need to meet a girl from school, just act the way you would have, this is what I felt. Just act confident, nice and polite, but don't make out loud or anything like that you will get the woman's feeling of shock.

At school you will hear her voice on a TV programme and get the message, you will get the message to you that no matter what you need her to become your friend. This is not only fun but you do not have as much time on your mind as you do you need. I did not know I really wanted to be my own best friend, but if I would not be the person I was and feel I need to feel better just don't do it.

Good luck, and have fun learning from your experiences, I love you and love you, and I am truly sorry that you are hurting this way.<|endoftext|>
